{"title_page": "Tokyu 3020 series", "text_new": "{{short description|Japanese electric multiple unit train type}}\n{{Infobox train\n| name             = Tokyu 3020 series\n| image            = File:3022F.jpg\n| imagesize        = \n| caption          = A 3020 series train (right) in September 2019\n| manufacturer     = [[J-TREC]]\n| factory          = \n| family           = \n| replaced         = \n| yearconstruction = 2019 \u2013 \n| yearservice      = 5 January 2020\n| refurbishment    =\n| yearscrapped     =\n| numberconstruction= \n| numberbuilt      = 16 vehicles \n| numberservice    = \n| numberpreserved  =\n| numberscrapped   =\n| formation        = 6 cars per trainset\n| fleetnumbers     =\n| capacity         =\n| operator         = [[File:TokyuLogotype.svg|18px|alt=Tokyu logo]] [[Tokyu Corporation]]\n| depots           = \n| lines            = [[Tokyu Meguro Line]]\n| carbody          = \n| carlength        = \n| width            = \n| height           = \n| floorheight      = \n| doors            = 4 pairs per side\n| maxspeed         = \n| weight           =\n| acceleration     = \n| deceleration     = \n| traction         = \n| poweroutput      =\n| aux              =\n| powersupply      =\n| hvac             =\n| electricsystem   = 1,500 V DC [[overhead catenary]]\n| collectionmethod = [[Pantograph (transport)|Pantograph]]\n| bogies           = \n| brakes           =\n| safety           =\n| coupling         =\n| multipleworking  =\n| gauge            = {{RailGauge|1067mm|lk=on}}\n}}\n\nThe {{Nihongo|'''Tokyu 3020 series'''|\u6771\u60253020\u7cfb|T\u014dky\u016b 3020-kei}} is an [[electric multiple unit]] (EMU) commuter train type operated by the [[private railway]] operator [[Tokyu Corporation]] in Japan for services on the [[Tokyu Meguro Line]].\n\n==Design==\nThe 3020 series trains share a common design with the [[Tokyu 2020 series]] and [[Tokyu 6020 series]] trains used on the [[Den-en-toshi Line]] and [[T\u014dky\u016b \u014cimachi Line|\u014cimachi Line]].<ref name=\"mynavi26032019\">{{cite web |last=Kamishin |first=Daisuke |url=https://news.mynavi.jp/article/20190326-tokyu3020/ |title=\u6771\u6025\u96fb\u92443020\u7cfb\u3001\u76ee\u9ed2\u7dda\u306b\u65b0\u578b\u8eca\u4e21 - \u4eca\u79cb\u304b\u30896\u4e21\u7de8\u6210\u30923\u7de8\u6210\u5c0e\u5165 |trans-title=Tokyu Corporation 3020 series, new trains on Meguro Line - 3 trains introduced in 6 car formation from this fall |language=Japanese |date=March 26, 2019 |website=news.mynavi.jp |publisher=Mynavi Corporation |access-date=July 24, 2019 |quote=}}</ref>\n\n==Formation==\nThe trains are formed as six-car sets,<ref name=\"mynavi26032019\"/> and are scheduled to be lengthened to eight cars in 2022 as part of Tokyu Corporation's strategy to cope with high demand on the Meguro Line.<ref name=\"mynavi20190326-2\">{{cite web |last=Kamishin |first=Daisuke |url=https://news.mynavi.jp/article/20190326-tokyumeguroline/ |title=\u6771\u6025\u96fb\u9244\u3001\u65b0\u578b\u8eca\u4e21\u542b\u3080\u76ee\u9ed2\u7dda26\u7de8\u6210\u30928\u4e21\u5316 - 2022\u5e74\u5ea6\u4e0a\u671f\u304b\u3089 |trans-title=Tokyu Corporation, the Meguro Line 26 sets including new vehicles will be eight cars - from the first half of fiscal 2022 |language=Japanese |date=March 26, 2019 |website=news.mynavi.jp |publisher=Mynavi Corporation |access-date=July 24, 2019}}</ref> During trial runs the six-car set was formed as follows.<ref name=\"railfan29062019\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Car\n! 1 !! 2 !! 3 !! 4 !! 5 !! 6 \n|-\n! Designation\n| Kuha 3122 || Deha 3222 || Deha 3322 || Deha 3622 || Deha 3722 || Kuha 3822\n|}\n\n==Interior==\nPassenger accommodation consists of high-back seating.<ref name=\"mynavi26032019\"/> The trains are also fitted with [[security camera]]s and [[air purifier]]s.<ref name=\"railfan26032019\">{{cite web |url=https://railf.jp/news/2019/03/26/150000.html |title=\u6771\u6025\u76ee\u9ed2\u7dda\u306b3020\u7cfb\u3092\u5c0e\u5165\u3078\u6771\u6025\u65b0\u6a2a\u6d5c\u7dda\u958b\u696d\u307e\u3067\u306b8\u4e21\u7de8\u6210\u5316\u3082\u5b9f\u65bd |trans-title=To introduce 3020 series to the Tokyu Meguro Line Also 8-car organization by the opening of the Tokyu Shin-Yokohama Line |date=March 26, 2019 |work=Japan Railfan Magazine Online |publisher=Koyusha Co., Ltd. |location=Japan |language=Japanese |accessdate=July 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\nOn March 26, 2019 Tokyu Corporation announced the introduction of new 3020 series trains on their Meguro Line.<ref name=\"mynavi26032019\"/> The first set of eight cars was delivered in April 2019.<ref name=\"railfan10042019\">{{cite web |url=https://railf.jp/news/2019/04/10/173000.html |title=\u76ee\u9ed2\u7dda\u75283020\u7cfb\u304c\u7532\u7a2e\u8f38\u9001\u3055\u308c\u308b |trans-title=Meguro Line 3020 series will be transported |date=April 10, 2019 |work=Japan Railfan Magazine Online |publisher=Koyusha Co., Ltd. |location=Japan |language=Japanese |accessdate=July 24, 2019}}</ref> A second set of eight cars was transferred from [[J-TREC]] in Yokohama to Nagatsuta in May 2019.<ref name=\"railfan31052019\">{{cite web |url=https://railf.jp/news/2019/05/31/150000.html |title=\u6771\u60253020\u7cfb\u7b2c2\u7de8\u6210\u304c\u7532\u7a2e\u8f38\u9001\u3055\u308c\u308b |trans-title=The Tokyu 3020 series second formation will be transported |date=May 31, 2019 |work=Japan Railfan Magazine Online |publisher=Koyusha Co., Ltd. |location=Japan |language=Japanese |accessdate=July 24, 2019}}</ref> Trial runs on the Den-en-toshi Line began in June 2019.<ref name=\"railfan29062019\">{{cite web |url=https://railf.jp/news/2019/06/29/203000.html |title=\u6771\u60253020\u7cfb\u304c6\u4e21\u7de8\u6210\u3067\u8a66\u904b\u8ee2\u3092\u5b9f\u65bd |trans-title=The Tokyu 3020 series carries out trial operation with a six-car train |date=June 29, 2019 |work=Japan Railfan Magazine Online |publisher=Koyusha Co., Ltd. |location=Japan |language=Japanese |accessdate=July 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\nThe first 3020 series set entered revenue service on January 5, 2020.{{cn|date=January 2020}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscat}}\n* [https://www.tokyu.co.jp/image/news/pdf/20190326-3.pdf Official news release] {{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{Tokyu trainsets}}\n\n[[Category:Electric multiple units of Japan]]\n[[Category:Tokyu Corporation|3020]]\n[[Category:Train-related introductions in 2019]]\n[[Category:J-TREC rolling stock]]\n\n[[ja:\u6771\u60253020\u7cfb\u96fb\u8eca]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Japanese electric multiple unit train type}}\n{{Infobox train\n| name             = Tokyu 3020 series\n| image            = File:3022F.jpg\n| imagesize        = \n| caption          = A 3020 series train (right) in September 2019\n| manufacturer     = [[J-TREC]]\n| factory          = \n| family           = \n| replaced         = \n| yearconstruction = 2019 \u2013 \n| yearservice      = 5 January 2020\n| refurbishment    =\n| yearscrapped     =\n| numberconstruction= \n| numberbuilt      = 16 vehicles \n| numberservice    = \n| numberpreserved  =\n| numberscrapped   =\n| formation        = 6 cars per trainset\n| fleetnumbers     =\n| capacity         =\n| operator         = [[File:TokyuLogotype.svg|18px|alt=Tokyu logo]] [[Tokyu Corporation]]\n| depots           = \n| lines            = [[Tokyu Meguro Line]]\n| carbody          = \n| carlength        = \n| width            = \n| height           = \n| floorheight      = \n| doors            = 4 pairs per side\n| maxspeed         = \n| weight           =\n| acceleration     = \n| deceleration     = \n| traction         = \n| poweroutput      =\n| aux              =\n| powersupply      =\n| hvac             =\n| electricsystem   = 1,500 V DC [[overhead catenary]]\n| collectionmethod = [[Pantograph (transport)|Pantograph]]\n| bogies           = \n| brakes           =\n| safety           =\n| coupling         =\n| multipleworking  =\n| gauge            = {{RailGauge|1067mm|lk=on}}\n}}\n\nThe {{Nihongo|'''Tokyu 3020 series'''|\u6771