{"title_page": "Joe D'Cruz", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = R. N. Joe D'Cruz\n| image        = \n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   = 1969\n| birth_place  = [[Uvari]], [[Tirunelveli District]], [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]]\n| death_date   = \n| other_names  = \n| occupation   = [[Novelist]], [[Ship management]]\n| spouse       = Sasikala\n| children     = \n| parents      = \n| yearsactive  = \n}}\n\n[[File:Joe D'cruz.jpg|alt=|thumb]]\n'''R. N. Joe D'Cruz''' is a [[Tamil language|Tamil]] writer, novelist and documentary film director from [[Tamil Nadu]], India. He won the [[Sahitya Akademi award]] in 2013 in the [[List of Sahitya Akademi Award winners for Tamil|Tamil language]] category for his novel ''Korkai''. He is the Tamil Nadu state president of [[Samskrita Bharati]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/TN-Sanskrit-Learning-Gets-Face-in-Joe-DCruz/2015/09/06/article3012913.ece | title = TN Sanskrit Learning Gets Face in Joe D'Cruz|work = New Indian Express | date = 6 September 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/chennai/people-have-been-misled-on-sanskrit-for-60-years/article7643813.ece | title = People have been misled on Sanskrit for 60 years|work = The Hindu | date = 12 September 2015}}</ref>\n\nJoe D'Cruz has also been a managerial-executive in the shipping industry for a long time and is currently a member of the National Shipping Board of  the Ministry of Shipping, Government of India.<ref name=\"thehindu.com\">http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/joe-dcruz-appointed-to-shipping-board/article19948086.ece</ref>\n\n== Life ==\nJoe D'Cruz was born in a [[Roman Catholic]] [[Paravar]] family in [[Uvari]], a coastal village in [[Tirunelveli District]] of [[Tamil Nadu]]. He did his schooling in Uvari and [[Idaiyangudi]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.vikatan.com/anandavikatan/En-Vikatan---Madurai-Edition/17525-.html | title=\u0b8e\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b8a\u0bb0\u0bcd! | publisher=[[Ananda Vikatan]] | date=28 March 2012 | accessdate=19 December 2013 | language=Tamil}}</ref> He graduated with an M.A.(Economics) at [[Loyola College, Chennai]] and did his M.Phil at [[St. Joseph's College, Tiruchirapalli]]. He is married to Sasikala and has two children.<ref name=\"Dina Thanthi\">{{cite news | url=http://www.dailythanthi.com/taxonomy/term/92253 | title=\u0b86\u0bb0\u0bcd.\u0b8e\u0ba9\u0bcd.\u0b9c\u0bcb\u2013\u0b9f\u0bbf\u2013\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bc2\u0bb8\u0bcd | work=[[Dina Thanthi]] | date=19 December 2013 | accessdate=19 December 2013 | language=Tamil}}</ref> He has been working in the shipping industry for more than two decades.\n\n== Works ==\nJoe D'Cruz published a Tamil poetry compilation, ''Pulambazhkal'', in 2004. His [[Sahitya Akademi award]]-winning novel ''Korkai'' was originally published in 2009 and prior to that his 2005 novel ''Aazhi Soozh Ulagu'' was awarded the Tamil Nadu state government literary award<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/131219/news-current-affairs/article/joe-d%E2%80%99cruz-wins-sahitya-akademi-award | title=Joe D'Cruz wins Sahitya Akademi award | work=Deccan Chronicle | date=19 December 2013 | accessdate=19 December 2013}}</ref> and [[The Tamil Literary Garden|Tamil Literary Garden]] award. Both his novels are based on history and the lives of Parathavar fishermen of Tamil Nadu.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-national/tp-tamilnadu/sailing-high-as-a-writer/article2291463.ece | title=Sailing high as a writer | work=The Hindu | date=25 July 2011 | accessdate=18 December 2013}}</ref> The first novel ''Aazhi Soozh Ulagu'' dealt with the lives of fishermen who used [[catamaran]]s and their [[Paravar#Arrival of the Portuguese and Christianity|conversion to Christianity]]. The second novel titled ''Korkai'' refers to [[Korkai]], an ancient port city ruled by [[Early Pandyan Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://archaeologyindia.com/korkai.asp | title=KORKAI | publisher=[[Archaeological Survey of India]] | accessdate=20 December 2013 | archive-url=https://archive.is/20131220122946/http://archaeologyindia.com/korkai.asp | archive-date=20 December 2013 | url-status=dead }}</ref> It documented 20th-century history of the people in the region. It is considered as a well-researched historical novel.<ref name=\"tnie\">{{cite web | url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/chennai/article1403605.ece | title=The Parathavas have come full circle | work=The New Indian Express | date=2 January 2013 | accessdate=20 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nHe also filmed documentary films such as ''Vidiyatha Pozhuthukal'' (2008), ''Towards Dawn'' (2010).<ref name=\"Dina Thanthi\" /> His films mostly based on sufferings of Tamil fishermen. He wrote the dialogue for Tamil movie [[Maryan (film)|Maryan]]. He opposed [[Kudankulam Nuclear Power Plant|Kudankulam nuclear power project]], arguing it will affect the livelihood of the fishermen.<ref name=\"tnie\" /><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/sons-of-the-sea-show-true-grit/article4154435.ece | title=Sons of the sea show true grit | work=The Hindu | date=2 December 2012 | accessdate=20 December 2013}}</ref>\n\nHe has also expressed his reservations on the upcoming International Container Transhipment Terminal at Enayam, [[Kanyakumari District]]. He is in favour of developing existing ports over initiating new port projects in India.<ref name=\"thehindu.com\"/>\n\n==Support for LGBTQIA+ Community==\nJoe D'Cruz along with writer [[Aravindan Neelakandan]] supported the initiatives of [[Gopi Shankar Madurai]] and served on the advisory board of Srishti Madurai under [[Anjali Gopalan]], [[Bracha Ettinger]].<ref>http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/madurai/Its-a-great-honour-to-be-awarded-for-book-on-gender-variants-Gopi-Shankar/articleshow/38769130.cms</ref>\n\n== Threats and Professional Censure for Supporting Narendra Modi ==\nThe Indian Express<ref name=\"iemodi\"/> reported that Joe D'Cruz received threats and hate-mail after he expressed support for the BJP PM Candidate in the 2014 Lok Sabha elections, Mr. [[Narendra Modi]], on his Facebook page. A translation of his work ''\u2018Aazhi Soozh Ulagu\u2019'' into English, was also halted in retaliation by his publisher Navyana and the translator Geetha.<ref name=\"hindumodi\"/><ref name=modidna/><ref name=hindunavayana/><ref name=navayana/><ref name=navayana2/>\n\n==Bibliography==\n\n===Novels===\n*''Aazhi Soozh Ulagu''\n*''Korkai''\n*''Verpiditha Vilai Nilangal''\n*''Asthinapuram''\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|colwidth=30em|refs=\n<ref name=\"iemodi\">{{cite web | url= http://indianexpress.com/article/india/politics/celebrity-tamil-novelist-supports-narendra-modi-gets-threat/ | title=Celebrity Tamil novelist supports Narendra Modi, gets threat | work=The Indian Express | date=13 April 2014 | accessdate=13 April 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"hindumodi\">{{cite web | url=  http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/promodi-stand-stops-dcruz-book-release/article5909141.ece | title=Pro-Modi stand stops D\u2019Cruz book release | work=The Hindu | date=14 April 2014 | accessdate= 14 April 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=modidna>{{citation | url = http://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-it-is-fundamentalism-of-the-people-who-wear-liberal-mask-joe-d-cruz-on-cancellation-of-book-translation-due-to-his-support-for-narendra-modi-1978449 | title = It is fundamentalism of the people who wear liberal mask: Joe D'Cruz on cancellation of book translation due to his support for Narendra Modi | author=Mehernaz Patel | newspaper = DNA | date = 15 April 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=hindunavayana>{{citation | url = http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/navayana-defends-dcruz-book-release-decision/article5909147.ece | title = Navayana defends D\u2019Cruz book release decision\n | newspaper = The Hindu | date = April 14, 2014}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=navayana>{{citation | url = https://navayana.org/blog/2014/04/13/the-unraveling-of-joe-dcruz/?v=c86ee0d9d7ed | title = The Unraveling of Joe D\u2019Cruz | publisher = Navayana | access-date = April 6, 2020 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=navayana2>{{citation | url = http://navayana.org/the-storm-in-the-dcruz-ocean/ | title = The Storm in the D\u2019Cruz Ocean | publisher = Navayana }}{{Dead link|date=April 2020 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb name|id=5647217|name=R.N. Joe D'Cruz}}\n\n{{Sahitya Akademi Award For Tamil}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:D'Cruz, Joe}}\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Tamil-language writers]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Sahitya Akademi Award in Tamil]]\n[[Category:St. Joseph's College, Tiruchirappalli alumni]]\n[[Category:Year of birth missing (living people)]]\n[[Category:People from Tirunelveli district]]\n[[Category:Writers from Tamil Nadu]]\n[[Category:Loyola College, Chennai alumni]]\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = R. N. Joe D'Cruz\n| image        = \n| birth_name   = \n| birth_date   = 1969\n| birth_place  = [[Uvari]], [[Tirunelveli District]], [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]]\n| death_date   = \n| other_names  = \n| occupation   = [[Novelist]], [[Ship management]]\n| spouse       = Sasikala\n| children     = \n| parents      = \n| yearsactive  = \n}}\n\n[[File:Joe D'cruz.jpg|alt=|thumb]]\n'''R. N. Joe D'Cruz''' is a [[Tamil language|Tamil]] writer, novelist and documentary film director from [[Tamil Nadu]], India. He won the [[Sahitya Akademi award]] in 2013 in the [[List of Sahitya Akademi Award winners for Tamil|Tamil language]] category for his novel ''Korkai''. He is the Tamil Nadu state president of [[Samskrita Bharati]].<ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/states/tamil_nadu/TN-Sanskrit-Learning-Gets-Face-in-Joe-DCruz/2015/09/06/article3012913.ece | title = T